news.title: Embassy REIT to invest Rs 3,700 crore to develop 7.2 million sq ft office space: CEO
news.para: Amit Shetty, CEO, Embassy Office Parks REIT   outlines how the company is gearing up for its next growth cycle with a ₹3,700 crore development pipeline, while maintaining a 51 million sq ft portfolio with 93% value occupancy and strong leasing metrics.

news.title: Six buildings sealed in Ludhiana’s push against illegal structures
news.para: Ludhiana Municipal Corporation has sealed six buildings for non-compliance with demands for pending dues and rectification of illegal structures. This stern crackdown follows directives from MC Commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal to expedite civic fee recovery and enforce strict measures against unauthorized constructions. Residents are urged to obtain official approval before commencing any construction work.

news.title: Jaipur civic body seals Walled City building for three months
news.para: Jaipur Municipal Corporation sealed a property on Chaura Rasta for three months due to unauthorized renovation work. The owner failed to obtain permission for ongoing alterations to the heritage structure, despite repeated notices and temporary halts. This action follows the civic body's resolution for stringent measures against such violations.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: QUAD project at Technopark gets environmental clearance
news.para: Technopark's ambitious QUAD project in Thiruvananthapuram has received formal environmental clearance. This integrated IT and office campus, spanning 8.5 lakh sq ft, will feature a green IT building and aims to be a live-work-play environment for 6,000 IT professionals.  Construction is expected to proceed swiftly as Technopark will own the building, with co-developer selection nearing completion.

news.title: Kartik Aaryan's parents buy office unit in Mumbai for ₹10.8 crore
news.para: Kartik Aaryan's family has secured an office space in Vile Parle, Mumbai. Priced at ₹10.83 crore and finalized in November, the property offers a carpet area of 1,228 sq ft along with two parking spots.

news.title: HRX Digitech LLP buy four commercial units worth ₹10.90 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Rakesh and Hrithik Roshan's company HRX Digitech LLP has acquired four commercial properties in Andheri West, Mumbai. The total deal amounted to ₹10.90 crore. These transactions were registered in November 2025. The properties are located in Yura Business Park Phase 2.

news.title: Embassy REIT acquires office asset in Bengaluru for ₹8,520 million
news.para: Embassy REIT has acquired a prime office property in Bengaluru. The deal is valued at over ₹850 crore. This grade-A asset is fully leased, ensuring steady income. This move is expected to boost the company's portfolio and cash flow visibility.

news.title: Address Maker secures ₹200 crore capital partnership from AI Growth
news.para: Address Maker has teamed up with AI Growth to secure ₹200 crore for vital capital investments. This funding will empower strategic land purchases and enable joint development ventures.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to redevelop residential project in Matunga, Mumbai
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers will redevelop a residential project in Matunga, Mumbai. The company plans significant growth through new launches and ongoing projects until 2030. This expansion is supported by a strong financial position following a recent rights issue.  The developer is set to scale up its operations and acquire new opportunities.

news.title: All unsafe buildings in Cuttack to be demolished: Odisha housing minister
news.para: Cuttack's unsafe buildings will be demolished to ensure public safety, announced Housing Minister Krushna Chandra Mahapatra. A special committee is surveying all 59 wards to identify vulnerable residential and commercial structures. Owners will receive notices before demolition, a move prompted by a recent balcony collapse that claimed three lives.

news.title: IL&FS could get 25% rise in valuation for its headquarters in BKC
news.para: IL&FS headquarters in BKC may see a 25% price increase. The NCLT allowed a valuation revision due to Mumbai's real estate growth. Brookfield's subsidiary Chronos must renew its performance guarantee within 30 days. This follows a dispute over the original bid terms from 2022. New valuations could reach ₹2,000-2,500 crore.

news.title: Apartment owners demand action to update Karnataka apartment law
news.para: Federation representing 1.5 million residents’ urges govt to table KAOMA in Belagavi, citing chaos from outdated laws and unresolved ownership disputes.

news.title: Carlyle Group in talks to buy majority stake in Nido Home Finance
news.para: Carlyle Group is reportedly in discussions to acquire a majority stake in Indian home mortgage firm Nido Home Finance Ltd., with an initial investment of approximately $300 million. This move signifies Carlyle's intent to increase its presence in India's expanding financial services sector, particularly in housing finance.

news.title: Co-developers cleared to revive two stalled projects in Greater Noida
news.para: Greater Noida Authority has approved co-developers for two stalled housing projects, Nobal Buildtech and Gayatri Hospitality & Realcon, under UP's rehabilitation policy. Birla Estates will co-develop the Nobal Buildtech project, while Floral Homes will take over the Gayatri Hospitality project, backed by a Rs 300 crore commitment from SWAMIH Investment Fund.

news.title: Ghaziabad: NBCC to oversee revamp of ‘unsafe’ Tulsi Niketan flats
news.para: NBCC will lead the redevelopment of Ghaziabad's unsafe Tulsi Niketan colony, signing an MoU with GDA. The project, to be completed in two phases within three years, aims to rebuild dilapidated flats. Despite previous failed attempts due to resident reluctance, NBCC is now set to manage the construction.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders builder to pay 11% interest to buyer for delay in handover of flat
news.para: Haryana RERA has ordered Godrej Real View Developers to pay 10.8% annual compensation to a Lucknow couple for delayed possession of their flat in Godrej Meridien-I. The authority rejected the builder's force majeure claims, including COVID-19 and pollution bans, stating recurring curbs were foreseeable. The couple is entitled to monthly interest until possession is handed over.

news.title: Panel seeks fast-track courts to expedite insolvency cases
news.para: A parliamentary panel urges the government to establish special fast-track courts and bolster the National Company Law Tribunal. This aims to clear a massive backlog of insolvency cases and speed up company rescues. The committee also proposed an advance ruling system for greater certainty. These measures are expected to improve the resolution process and protect creditor interests.

news.title: Reforms help DDA to garner nearly ₹1,500 crore in plot e-auction: Delhi Raj Niwas
news.para: The recent e-auction held by the Delhi Development Authority for 81 plots broke records, generating revenues that far surpassed the base price, more than doubling expectations. Reforms from Lt Governor V K Saxena, such as adjustments to reserve price multiplication factors, bidders flocked in greater numbers.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance promoter entity sells 2% stake for ₹1,588 crore
news.para: Bajaj Finance has divested a 2 percent stake in Bajaj Housing Finance for Rs 1,588 crore. This shift lowers their ownership in the housing finance arm. Notably, Bajaj Housing Finance has also announced an impressive 18 percent increase in profits for the September quarter, alongside a rise in overall income.

news.title: Telangana CM seeks Hudco loans for Hyderabad metro and Future City
news.para: Telangana Chief Minister Revanth Reddy has requested Hudco Chairman Sanjay Kulshrestha to provide loans at reduced interest rates for key state development projects. These include the proposed Bharat Future City, Hyderabad Metro Rail expansion, and the Indiramma housing program. Kulshrestha has agreed to review high-interest loans taken by the previous government and expedite funds for additional housing units.
